he Tribune Star in Terra Haute  Ind  visitation will be from 4 p m  to 8 p m  on Nov  10 at the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints  located at 1845 North 6 1 2th St  in Terre Haute  Ind  The funeral will take place at 2 p m  on Nov  11 at Terre Haute South Vigo High School  with burial following at High Lawn Cemetery  In lieu of flowers  donations can be made to the Dale Russel Griffin Memorial Fund at the Wabash Valley Community Foundation  located at 2901 Ohio Blvd  Terre Haute  Ind  Additional information concerning the memorial fund is available by calling  812  232 2234    LEXINGTON  Va  Oct  29  2009   VMI alumnus Sgt  Dale R  Griffin  29  was killed by a roadside bomb while on duty in southern Afghanistan Tuesday  Oct  27  His remains were among those of 18 Americans who died in Afghanistan that were received at Dover Air Force Base  Del  Wednesday night  Griffin matriculated with the Class of 2003  and attended VMI for three semesters  A wrestler  he won his weight class in the 2000 All Academy Wrestling Championship  and was named the tournament s Most Outstanding Wrestler   He was a tough kid  said John S  Trudgeon  VMI s head wrestling coach   To win particularly in that tournament as a true freshman and to be named outstanding wrestler for the tournament as a true freshman  he had to be tough  I m not surprised he ended up in the Army and in Afghanistan  Funeral arrangements for the Terre Haute  Ind  native are pending   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 2